The paper proposes a machine learning model for multi-step passenger demand forecasting in on-demand vehicle sharing services. The model uses a graph structure to capture spatial-temporal dependencies and a hierarchical graph convolutional structure to model both spatial and temporal correlations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a machine learning model for a specific task. The use of graph structures and attention mechanisms also suggests that the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.CV. Finally, the paper's focus on multi-step prediction and temporal dependencies suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS.
